{"@context": "http://schema.org", "@type": "Movie", "url": "/title/tt1058017/", "name": "The Invention of Lying", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU2OTQzOTc1Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDM5MDE4Mg@@._V1_.jpg", "genre": ["Comedy", "Fantasy", "Romance"], "contentRating": "PG-13", "actor": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0315041/", "name": "Ricky Gervais"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0004950/", "name": "Jennifer Garner"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm1706767/", "name": "Jonah Hill"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0127373/", "name": "Louis C.K."}], "director": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0315041/", "name": "Ricky Gervais"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm2816668/", "name": "Matthew Robinson"}], "creator": [{"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0315041/", "name": "Ricky Gervais"}, {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm2816668/", "name": "Matthew Robinson"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0002663/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0023815/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0194736/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0237137/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0226345/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0071668/"}, {"@type": "Organization", "url": "/company/co0265519/"}], "description": "The Invention of Lying is a movie starring Ricky Gervais, Jennifer Garner, and Jonah Hill. A comedy set in a world where no one has ever lied, until a writer seizes the opportunity for personal gain.", "datePublished": "2009-10-02", "keywords": "truth,lie,screenwriter,heaven,genetics", "aggregateRating": {"@type": "AggregateRating", "ratingCount": 129692, "bestRating": "10.0", "worstRating": "1.0", "ratingValue": "6.4"}, "review": {"@type": "Review", "itemReviewed": {"@type": "CreativeWork", "url": "/title/tt1058017/"}, "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "delibebek"}, "dateCreated": "2010-08-11", "inLanguage": "English", "name": "Good vehicle for (and by) Gervais", "reviewBody": "I was pleasantly surprised by this film. From a simple premise as \"lying doesn't exist\" it develops into a thoughtful tale with a touch of satire. On the one hand it exposes early on the basic first impressions we all have of each other and of situations we find ourselves in. On the other, it touches on the importance of being honest about what we know and especially honest about what we don't know.\n\nI could examine all the inconsistencies inherent to a concept like this. One would think that without the concept of duplicity, we should be far more advanced than we currently are. One would also think that without lying, there would be no imagination and therefore very few scientific discoveries and advances. The story requires that you don't think about that too much, just to enjoy the script as it moves along.\n\nGervais carries the film along as planned, in his quiet, self-effacing way. The humor won't have you rolling on the floor, but the frankness of the casual insights should make anyone snicker with self-awareness at the truth of it all.", "reviewRating": {"@type": "Rating", "worstRating": "1", "bestRating": "10", "ratingValue": "7"}}, "duration": "PT1H40M", "trailer": {"@type": "VideoObject", "name": "The Invention of Lying: UK Trailer", "embedUrl": "/video/imdb/vi2028667417", "thumbnail": {"@type": "ImageObject", "contentUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTgxMzE2OTM0NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDc1NTg4MjE@._V1_.jpg"}, "thumbnailUrl": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTgxMzE2OTM0NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDc1NTg4MjE@._V1_.jpg", "description": "Trailer for The Invention of Lying", "uploadDate": "2009-07-01T09:53:20Z"}, "cast_and_character": [{"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm0315041/?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Ricky Gervais"}, "character_and_episodes": [{"url": "/title/tt1058017/characters/nm0315041?ref_=tt_cl_t1", "name": "Mark Bellison"}]}, {"actor": {"@type": "Person", "url": "/name/nm1706767/?ref_=tt_cl_t3", "name":